## Design system contract (Make + EDS, not Figma MCP)

This section encodes the **same intent** as project-level “design system rules” in tools like Figma’s [Create Design System Rules](https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/skill-figma-create-design-system-rules/) — *where things live, what to reuse, what never to hardcode* — but RAD’s **visual source of truth is the tracked UIUX pack + EDS**, not MCP `get_design_context`.

| Figma-rules idea | RAD equivalent |
| --- | --- |
| Fetch structured design + screenshot before coding | **Read** `artifacts/uiux-reference/` (`shell.jsx`, `screens/*.jsx`, `styles.css`) and **`artifacts/docs/screen-specs-*-v1.md`**, **`artifacts/docs/design-system-spec.md`**; optional legacy dump in gitignored `src/make-import/` |
| Token / component discovery | **`design-system-spec.md`** (inventory + gaps); live primitives in **`src/components/ui/`**; tokens in **`src/app.css`** (Make theme + `--gv-*` Studio) |
| Do not bolt on duplicate libraries | **IMPORTANT:** `src/components/ui/` **is** the library — same as elsewhere in this file |
| Asset discipline | Match UIUX reference + self-host fonts per `frontend-make.mdc`; do **not** add icon packages to duplicate what `lucide-react` already covers |

**Before changing layout, colors, or adding a “new” UI primitive:** Check `design-system-spec.md` and existing `src/components/ui/` — extend or compose; do not introduce a parallel component set.

When **native** mode is active, brand colors/types that land in **`shared/colors.ts`** and `mobile/global.css` must **stay aligned** with EDS §5 and web tokens (see `mobile-developer.md` Foundation).

