## Design Tokens (Make → Tailwind)

- Make's code output defines the visual design. Make uses CSS custom properties with Tailwind v4's `@theme inline` syntax for design tokens — keep this CSS-based approach during Foundation. Do not migrate tokens to `tailwind.config.ts`. Copy Make's theme CSS into `src/app.css`.
- All components use Tailwind utility classes referencing semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border-default`) — never raw hex codes, pixel sizes, or raw font sizes
- Never use `style={{}}` for token values — only `className` with Tailwind classes
- `style={{}}` is only permitted for genuinely dynamic values that can't be expressed as a token (e.g. `style={{ width: dynamicWidth + 'px' }}`)

## Component Rules

- Make's UI components (`src/components/ui/`) are the app's component library — do not add shadcn/ui, Radix, HeroUI, or any other library
- Additional shared components (EmptyState, ErrorBanner, SkeletonCard) built during Foundation live in `src/components/`
- Every component must implement all applicable states: default / loading / error / empty
- Custom component interfaces must match the spec in `artifacts/docs/design-system-spec.md`
- Import shared components from `src/components/` — never recreate one that already exists there
- Make's TSX is copied directly into route files. Do not modify visual structure — every Tailwind class, spacing, and layout stays as Make wrote it

## AI Slop Guard — Never ship these patterns

- No gradient backgrounds using purple, violet, or indigo
- No 3-column icon-in-circle feature grids
- No global `text-align: center` on headings or card content
- No uniform border-radius across all components — use the radius scale from design tokens
- No decorative blobs, wavy dividers, or floating shapes
- No generic hero copy: "Unlock the power of...", "Your all-in-one solution for...", "Revolutionize your..."
- No emoji as visual design elements
- No colored left-border accent cards as a default pattern
- No identical spacing between all elements — use the spacing scale intentionally
